<body>
    <form action="/kabini" method="get">
    <div id="nav">
        <form action="/search" method="get">
          <p id="p1">Kabini</p>
         </form>
         <hr style="border-color:black;position:relative;top: 70px;">
         <div id="i1">
            <img id="apimg" src="https://thetravelshots.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/kabini-884x420.jpg">
        </div>
        <br><br><br><br><br>
        <div id="i2">
            <h2><strong><center>INFORMATION</center></strong></h2>
            <hr style="width: 950px;height: 1.5px;background-color: black;"><br>
            <p>If you’re arriving by train, arrange for a taxi to meet you at the station for your onward journey to Kabini. <br>
                Those setting out from Ooty can follow the Bandipur, Gundlupet, Begur, Nugu Dam & Hand Post Circle for a shorter albeit bumpy route, or come via Mysore, which is a better road. <br>
                Guests from Mumbai, Delhi, Calcutta, Hyderabad, Madras etc., can arrive via Bangalore. <br>
                Guests from Trivandrum, Cochin & Calicut can come via Mananthavadi, along the Mysore Mananthavadi road. <br>
                Guests from Mangalore & Madikeri could come via Hunsur, H.D. Kote and Hand Post Circle.The resort is about 223 km from Bangalore and 73 km from Mysore, which is well connected by national and state highways. <br>
                </p>
            
        </div>
        <div id="i3">
            <center><h2>WEATHER</h2></center><br>
            <hr style="width: 360px;height: 1.5px;background-color: black;">
            <div class="icon">
            <h1><%=temp%>°C</h1><img src="/day/default.png" alt="" srcset="" id="image">
            </div>
            <h1 class="climate"><%=climate%></h1>
                <h2>Humidity : <%=humidity%>%<br><br>Wind Speed : <%=windspeed%>kmph</h2>
        </div>
        <div id="i4">
            <center><h2>TRANSPORTATION</h2></center><br>
            <hr style="width: 360px;height: 1.5px;background-color: black;"><br>
            <p> <img src="https://img.icons8.com/?size=1x&id=oOAYqE64W2MO&format=png" height="25px" width="25px" alt="">&nbsp;&nbsp;By Air-The nearest airport is the Mysore airport, which has flights connecting Bangalore and Mangalore<br><br>
                <img src="https://img.icons8.com/?size=1x&id=d8MqKVWJkyqN&format=png" alt="" height="25px" width="25px">&nbsp;&nbsp; By Train-Mysore Junction is the nearest railway station, with trains available to major cities.<br><br>
                <img src="https://img.icons8.com/?size=1x&id=f42OOoV1ACzO&format=png" alt="" height="25px" width="25px">&nbsp;&nbsp;By Road-The resort is about 223 km from Bangalore and 73 km from Mysore, which is well connected by national and state highways.</p>
        </div>
    </form>
    <script>
        
        let image=document.getElementById("image");

        let climate=document.querySelector(".climate").textContent;
        if(climate=="Mist"){
            image.src="/day/Mist.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Patchy rain possible"){
            image.src="/day/Patchy.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Moderate rain"){
            image.src="/day/Moderate.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Light rain shower"){
            image.src="/day/patchy.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Partly cloudy"){
            image.src="/day/default.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Cloudy"){
            image.src="/day/Cloudy.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Overcast"){
            image.src="/day/Cloudy.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Sunny"){
            image.src="/day/Sunny.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Clear"){
            image.src="/day/Sunny.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Thundery outbreaks possible"){
            image.src="/day/Thunderstorm.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Fog"){
            image.src="/day/Fog.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Light rain"){
            image.src="/day/Patchy.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Moderate or heavy rain shower"){
            image.src="/day/Heavy.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Light drizzle"){
            image.src="/day/Drizzle.png"
        }
    
</script>
